<!-- CONSTRUCTION-->
<hr><table border="0" cellspacing="0" width="600">
<tbody><tr><td valign="top" width="600"><font color="#c80000" face="Arial, helvetica" size="3"><b><u>Do-It-Yourself instructions </u></b></font><br><br>
<font face="Arial, helvetica" size="2">
ALTI-OSD module can be built in 2 versions : 
<li> Miniature Surface Mount Component (SMD) version, presented in this page,
</li><li> DIL through hole component version, for people who don't master SMD. 
<br>External pinout of both versions are identical.
<br>All data necessary to build the 2 versions are available in the table below.
<br><br>
</li></font>
</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<table border="0" width="600"><tbody><tr><td>
<table align="center" border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
  <tbody><tr>
     <td width="150"><font face="Arial, helvetica" size="2"><center><b></b></center></font></td>
      <td width="200"><font face="Arial, helvetica" size="2"><center><b>&nbsp;Miniature SMD version</b></center></font></td>
      <td width="200"><font face="Arial, helvetica" size="2"><center><b>&nbsp;Standard DIL version</b></center></font></td></tr>
  <tr><td><font face="Arial, helvetica" size="2"><center><b>Dimensions</b></center></font></td>
